meta.description: Delta Air Lines Delta Sky Club at Hartsfield–Jackson Atlanta International Airport (ATL), Concourse T. Learn more about the lounge: amenities, photos, review, opening hours, location.

lounge.name: Delta Air Lines Delta Sky Club
lounge.description: The Delta Sky Club is an award-winning retreat that allows relaxation, productivity, or both.

reviews.content: Very clean and plenty of space away from other passengers. Delta is doing a great job with implementing social distancing. Great views.
Lounge is just meh. Nothing special. Guest access is now $39 with the Amex Plat. What a jip.
Tasty and plentiful food options, knowledgeable and friendly bartender, numerous staff members to constantly ensure tidiness.
Updated lounge with more seating, refreshed food area and a wall of TVs for news, etc...
This is a pretty nice lounge with hot food options, there’s even a peanut butter machine!
This lounge has a nice, cozy layout and plenty of seating, but unfortunately, the kitchen is being renovated so there are no hot food offerings.
Very clean and well appointed club. Solid food and bar.
This lounge no longer offers day access unless you are flying Delta or have a credit card with lounge access agreement. Very disappointed. However, The Club ATL is just across the way.

The bar is small but efficient and they make up for it # of comfy chairs available. TONS of comfy arm chairs close to outlets and side tables. Ample small tables with bar stools. Quiet and not crowded.
One of the better Delta lounges in ATL. Good snack selection and spacious. Good availability of electrical outlets and wasn't too crowded.
Decent Sky Club. If you don't feel like lugging to the nicer C or F clubs, you'll be fine here. Nice if dated decor and good views.
Visited at 6:30 pm. Nice selection of hot and cold food options, a full bar, and non-alcoholic beverages. Quiet and plenty of space to spread out. A quality lounge.
Good, but small. Seats could be upgraded, but the service is excellent.
This is my favorite at ATL; cozy and rarely crowded.
Nice domestic lounge with basic amenities.
Standard lounge, very large seating area, some breakfast food including bagels, cereal, oatmeal, yogurt, fruit (sliced and whole), granola, etc.
Relatively small lounge with limited power plugs. Mediocre food selection: Oatmeal, cereal, bagels, fruit, and yogurt at breakfast.
Nice lounge, good size, but lacking in the food/snack department.
This lounge made me think of days of yesteryear with its retro decor. I rate this highly in spite of lack of service as I left with lots of good snacks!
Great lounge that's nice, clean, and spacious. What else can you ask for?
This is a large, fairly comfortable lounge. However, overall, it's quite unremarkable.
This lounge has nice snacks, a friendly bartender, and is very clean. Grab a seat by the window (with outlets) and watch the planes come in.
